Package: HTTPD
Version: 4.0.0
Maintainer: Soldier of FORTRAN <mainframed767@gmail.com>
Depends: MINIZIP UFSD
Homepage: https://github.com/mvslovers/httpd
Description: HTTP Server for MVS 3.8J

This is mvslovers/httpd 4.0: an HTTP/1.1 web server for MVS 3.8j,
originally by Mike Rayborn, evolved by Mike Grossmann. Version 4.0
adds keep-alive and chunked transfer encoding, replaces the Lua
configuration engine with a Parmlib member, and serves static files
from the UFSD filesystem (DOCROOT=/www). Its primary role is hosting
CGI modules -- notably MVSMF, the z/OSMF REST API (packaged
separately) -- loaded from its STEPLIB.

This package installs HTTPD.LINKLIB (HTTPD plus the HTTPJES2,
HTTPDM, HTTPDMTT, HTTPDSL and HTTPDSRV CGI modules), the STC
procedure into SYS2.PROCLIB(HTTPD), and the default configuration
into SYS2.PARMLIB(HTTPPRM0). It replaces the previous HTTPD package:
the 3.3.0 datasets (HTTPD.HTML, HTTPD.ICON, HTTPD.LUA, HTTPD.BREXX,
HTTPD.UFSDISK0) and any existing HTTPD.LINKLIB are deleted. CGI
modules installed by other packages (e.g. MVSMF) must be reinstalled
after reinstalling HTTPD.

Static content requires the UFSD package: UFSD provides the
filesystem server and the HTTPD.WEBROOT disk mounted at /www.

To start the server run '/S HTTPD' on the Hercules console; stop
with '/P HTTPD'. Console commands: '/F HTTPD,DISPLAY CONFIG|DISPLAY
STATS|HELP|SHUTDOWN'. Settings (port, workers, routes, auth) live in
SYS2.PARMLIB(HTTPPRM0); the default listener port is 8080.
